@NODE "Introduction" "Introduction"
@TOC "MAIN"

INTRODUCTION


How many times you lent something to someone and after many days you
forget to who was?


Or how many times someone has a debt with you for money or disks and
you forget it? (Or may be you are the debtor...)


LOCK'N RETRIEVE! is a Workbench utility that will help you to remind
your lendings like money, books, disks, hardware and other things
along general information about your friends, family, enemies and
other patterns of organic life.


The program acts like a normal address/phone manager but with a
special area where you will can add your notes. Unike other programs
of this kind you will have an option to set a password to keep secret
your personal information.


LOCK'N RETRIEVE! is very easy to use and we're sure you should learn
all its functions in a few minutes.


Remember that this software is @{"GIFTWARE" LINK "Why"}. If you like it just
send anything you wish to the poor @{"authors" LINK "Address"} who spent time
writting this program. Stuff concerning MANGA is welcome!!!
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Installation" "Installation"
@TOC "MAIN"

INSTALLATION


1.- LOCK'N RETRIEVE! PACKAGE... 

You should find the following files in this software package:

Lock'n_Retrieve!V1.11        - main program
Lock'n_Retrieve!V1.11.info   - program icon (4 colors)
Lock'n_Retrieve!.guide       - document. (use AmigaGuide or Multiview)
Lock'n_Retrieve!.guide.info  - documentation's icon
LR!Icon_8c.info              - optional 8 colors icon for main prog.
                               (drawed in 5 ms. by Lobsang Alvites)


2.- SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS...

In order to run the program you'll need the following:

   * Escom Amiga computer (for those people that believe the only
     computers in the world are ms-dos machines and may try to run
     this software on them, urgh!)

   * KickStart 2.04+ or higher (better if OS 3.x)
 
   * A Workbench screen opened with more than the ROM built-in size

   * At least 110 KB of free memory

   * To have a debtor in the sight...


3.- INSTALLING THE PROGRAM...

Very easy! Copy the program in any drawer you wish of your hard disk
or floppydisk and you are ready to execute it!

Important Note: every time LOCK'N RETRIEVE! is started it will attempt
        to load its preferences file from the 'S' directory located in
        your booting hard-disk or diskette. Make sure that directory
        already exists. Please refer to the "Snapshot Path" option in
        the @{"Menu" LINK "Menus"} section.


4.- COMMODITY SUPPORT...

If you have some extra memory you may consider to drag the program to
your WBStartup drawer to load the program every time you boot your
lovely Amiga. Lock'n Retrieve! will take about 105K of Fast-Ram (if
available) but you'll can quickly access it by pressing its hotkey or
using Exchange.

We suggest that you configure the program with a lower priority so
your computer doesn't slowdown. Please refer to your Workbench 3.0
User's Guide for more details about priority, hotkeys and Commodity.


5.- CONFIGURATIONS TESTED...

LOCK'N RETRIEVE! was fully tested in the following systems:

    - Amiga 500 + Workbench 2.05, 3 MB Ram
    - Amiga 500 + Workbench 3.1
    - Amiga 1200 + 4 MB Fast Ram, 120 HD
    - Amiga 1200 + Blizzard 1230-IV ('030-50Mhz) + 4 MB Fast
    - Amiga 4000 + VideoToaster well equipped

The program should run fine also in other configurations but if you
experience some problems with your system please @{"contact" LINK "Address"} us. Don't
forget to tell us your system configuration.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Windows and Gadgets" "Windows and Gadgets"
@TOC "MAIN"

WINDOW GADGETS AND BUTTONS


****** MAIN WINDOW : The RECORD gadgets (left side)

  - SURNAME, NAME, PHONES, ADDRESS
    In these text-gadgets you just type in the data. You can jump from
    one gadget to another by pressing TAB, RETURN or moving the mouse
    pointer over the gadget and pressing the left mouse button.

  - ADD
    This option will create a new empty record. You can enter up to
    100 records in the database.
 
  - KILL
    The actual record will be deleted and the previous record will
    become the current one. If you kill the last record and the
    database is now empty the program will go into ADD Record mode
    automatically.

  - FIND
    This option will popup the Search window, from which you can enter
    the text you wish to search across the whole database.
    Please refer to "Search Window" for more details.

  - [<<],[<],[>],[>>] (Move gadgets) 
    Pressing these gadgets you can move around the database. The first
    button (Fast Backward) will go back three records, the second
    button (Backward) will go back to the previous one, the third
    button (Forward) will put you in the next record, and the last
    button (Fast Forward) will advance by three records.

  - RECORD # [xxx]
    By clicking on this gadget you can enter the number of a record
    and jump quickly to it.

****** MAIN WINDOW : The LENDINGS gadgets (right side)

  - LENDINGS LIST (the big box in the right side)
    Pressing an item in this list you can modify it. You can't select
    other options (like moving to another record) until you press the
    return key.
    In you selected an item and you can't type the letters try
    pressing the string gadget below the lendings listview. If this
    doesn't work then try re-selecting the same item in the listview.

  - ADD
    Selecting this button you can append a new line in the lendings
    list. The new entries will be stored when you press TAB or RETURN
    keys. Lock'n Retrieve! can actually store 30 lines, so if there is
    no space left this button will be shadowed.

  - INSERT
    After selecting a debt/lending line you can insert a new one
    pressing this button. Note that the new entry will be inserted
    just in the position selected by you.

  - DELETE
    After selecting a debt/lending line you can delete it pressing
    this button. If the lending list is empty then this button will be
    unavailable to the user (shadowed).

  - CLEAR
    This gadget will empty the whole debts/lendings list but will NOT
    delete the other data like Surname, Name, etc. If the lendings
    list is already empty then the button will be shadowed.
    Before take action, the program will ask if you are sure to
    empty the whole list.

    NOTES:

    When entering a new debt/lending item the program will disable
    other gadgets in order to prevent some confusions.

    A new entry record will be accepted (stored in memory) ONLY when
    you select any of the Record gadgets or Open/Save options.
  
    INSERT and DELETE gadgets in the debts/lending area will be
    shadowed until some item is selected.

    The number of records availables is 100 and you can enter up to
    30 lending lines. If you need more space please contact us.

****** SEARCH WINDOW

  - FIND 
    In this gadget you can type the text you wish to search. Note that
    the program will search across  *all*  the fields of the database.
    This means that you can search also by lendings and debts.

  - CASE SENSITIVE
    This switch activate (or deactivate) the case sensitive match.
    As an example, suppose that in the database there is a woman
    called "Roberta", the case sensitive button is activated, and you
    type in the Find gagdet the name "roberta". After pressing the
    Search (or Next) button the result will be that the program has
    not found the name. Now, try deactivating the case sensitive
    switch and press again the Search button. This time the program
    will find her! In other words, this button activates or
    deactivates the lower/upper case comparisons.
 
  - SEARCH
    Pressing this button will start to search the typed text in the
    Find gadget from the beginning of the database (Record #001).
    If a match is found then the program will put you automatically
    in the Record found.

  - NEXT
    This button will begin to search from the next record instead of
    starting from the first. This option is useful in case the program
    found a match and you wish to continue searching for any other.

  - CANCEL
    Closes the Search window and return you to the main window. The
    search case sensitive status will be preserved (temporally).

****** CONFIGURATION WINDOW
  
  - PASSWORD ACTIVATED
    This button enable and disable the password. If it is checked then
    the program will ask a password every time someone try to open it.

  - PASSWORD
    These three gadgets are only availables if the previous Password
    is activated. To select a new password you must press a sequence
    of color buttons. If you make a mistake you should press the
    button "CLEAR" and then begin again pressing a sequence of color
    buttons. When you are sure of your new password you must press
    the button "ACCEPT" before saving or using the new configuration,
    otherwise the program will continue with the previous password.
    The password sequence can be long as you want.

  - FIELD TO SORT
    Pressing this gadget you can select which field the program must
    use to sort your database. It's very  *important*  that you select
    the sorting field  *before*  you start to fill the database
    because the sort routine currently implemented only sorts the new
    entries without checking previous one.
  
  - POPKEY
    Lock'n Retrieve! was designed as a commodity, so you can call it
    using a hotkey. This gadget allows you to modified the hotkey.
    Another way to modify the hotkey is changing the ToolTypes.
    Please refer your Workbench 3.0 User's Guide for more details on
    hotkeys, Commodity and ToolTypes.

  - SHOW WINDOW AFTER LOADING
    If checked Lock'n Retrieve! will popup its window every time you
    load it. If you installed the program in your WBStartup drawer
    then we suggest that you don't check it.

  - USE
    This button will use temporally the new settings  *without*
    saving them to disk.

  - SAVE
    This button will store the new settings in your hard disk or
    floppy disk. From now the program will use these settings every
    time is started.
    
    LAST MINUTE:

    There is not a Cancel button, so pay attention when modifying
    settings. If you press the window's Close gadget you will USE the
    new configuration.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Menus" "Menus"
@TOC "MAIN"

THE MENUS OPTIONS


****** PROJECT MENU

  - NEW
    This option will erase from memory the whole database and start a
    new one. Any database files will be preserved.

  - OPEN
    This option will show you a file requester to select the database
    file to load. The selected path and filename will be the new
    current working directory/filename.

  - SAVE
    Will save your database to the current directory selected and with
    the last filename selected. If you haven't choosed a one then the
    program will automatically use the default settings.

  - SAVE AS...
    Before saving, you may select a new path and a new filename for
    your database file. After saving, the selected filename will be
    the new current working directory/filename.
    After choosing the path and filename you may select "Snapshot
    Path" from the PREFERENCES MENU. This will set the new default
    path/filename and will allow the program to automatically load
    your database when started. Please refer to "Snapshot Path" for
    more details.

  - PRINT
    Prints the whole database using the current Workbench's printer
    configuration. You can except a better Print option in future
    upgrades.

  - ABOUT...
    Shows general information about Lock'n Retrieve!

  - QUIT
    Terminate your session with the program. Lock'n Retrieve! will
    show you three options: QUIT (exit to Workbench), SAVE FIRST
    (stores your database before exiting) and CANCEL (return to
    Lock'n Retrieve! window).

****** SEARCH MENU

  - FIND
    This option will show the Search Window. Please refer to this
    option for more details.

  - NEXT
    If you already entered some word to search you can continue
    searching it by selecting this option or pressing the shortcut.

****** PREFERENCES MENU

  - SNAPSHOT WINDOW
    This option will save the current Lock'n Retrieve!'s window
    position so every time it must popup its window it will do it in
    the selected location.

  - SNAPSHOT PATH
    Every time Lock'n Retrieve is started it will search for a file
    called "LR!.PREFS" in your 'S' directory from the booting disk.
    If the file was not found then it will use "SYS:S/LR!DEFAULT.LR"
    as the default database's path/filename and "#?.lr" as the file
    pattern match. You can change the default path/filename and a new
    pattern match by simple choosing a new one when opening or saving
    a database and then selecting the "SNAPSHOT PATH" function.
    From now, every time Lock'n Retrieve will be started it will try
    to load the new default database.

  - CONFIGURATION
    Selecting this option will open the configuration window. Here you
    can modify some basic options of Lock'n Retrieve! Please refer to
    this option for more details.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "ToolTypes" "ToolTypes Settings"
@TOC "MAIN"

TOOLTYPES SETTINGS


Commodity and ToolTypes are great functions implemented since releases
of Workbench 2.x and Workbench 3.x!

LOCK'N RETRIEVE! was designed to stay all the time in memory so you
can access it quickly by pressing any keys combination or calling it
via Exchange.

You can modify some settings like the hotkey and program's priority.
To do this you have to change the ToolTypes values. These settings are
stored in the Lock'n Retrieve!'s icon. Click only one time on the icon
and then select "Information" from the Workbench's Icons menu


CX_POPUP = [YES/NO] -> Shows Lock'n Retrieve! window every time you
           start it (example: CX_POPUP=YES).

CX_POPKEY = [keys] -> Defines the program's hotkey so you can call the
           program without reloading it (ex.: CX_POPKEY=CTRL RALT F1)
           LR! will popup when you press Control Right-Alt F1 keys.

CX_PRIORITY = [value] -> Defines the program priority in the Exchange
           program (example: CX_PRIORITY=0, CX_PRIORITY=3, etc.).

TASKPRI = [value] -> Defines the program's priority in the Workbench
           environment (example: TASKPRI=0, TASKPRI=10, where the
           value "0" (zero) is the highest priority).


Please refer to "Workbench 3.0 User's Guide" for more details about
Priority, Commodity, Icons and ToolTypes settings.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "History" "History"
@TOC "MAIN"

LOCK'N RETRIEVE! HISTORY


v1.00  (27.May.1995) : Is the first released version. It doesn't crash
        anymore the machine!

v1.00a (29.May.1995) : Size code was reduced. The program now uses ASL
        library for file requesters. Users can now save file pattern
        match in the preferences.

v1.10 (10.July.1995) : A lot of new stuff were added to the program:
        - Commodity support
        - ToolTypes support (thanks to Mark Tiffany's Blitz2-Includes)
        - Search Window was created (selective case sensitive)
        - Configuration Window was created        
        - Password protection / Security Window created 
        - sort routine improved
        - user can now select the field to sort database
        - Print option added
        - "Save First" option added when selecting Quit from menu  
        - Display-bug fixed in Last Record print routine.
        - loading/saving routine improved
        - better look!
        - code optimization: 70% of the program code is now performed
          via OS calls instead Blitz2's commands. New windows and
          options were added without increasing memory requirements.
          Previous version: 115K, this version: 105K!
        - The program's documentation was improved.

v1.11 (20.Dec.1995)  : The contact address changed because I (Lobsang)
          went to Germany at the Computer'95 messe and now I'm living
          in Italy. Hey, it's hard to get Amiga friends here! Sigh!
        - A stupid bug was reported and then fixed.
        - Lock'n Retrieve! is now GIFTWARE.



No more entries.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "FuturePlans" "FuturePlans"
@TOC "MAIN"

FUTURE PLANS


This new version of Lock'n Retrieve! (v1.11) looks far better than
the previous one (v1.00a) by light-years! and we hope that you like
all the improvements we made.

This time these are the points which we will be coding around...
but not all of them will be included in the next version...

    * A gadget to add automatically a separator bar in the lendings
      list..

    * If something changed in the database since the last saved then
      Lock'n Retrieve! will warn you before quitting the program.

    * If you select Find (or press its shortcut) and there is not a
      word to search then popups the Search window.

    * Window Position and Snapshot path function included in the
      configuration window.

    * Improved PRINT option and selective output (for ex. to a file)

    * Selective ammount of skip records when fast moving around
      the database.

    * A compressor (to crunch the size of the database file)

    * Support for -POWER-UP!-> board from phase 5 Digital Products (!!)
      (if somebody needs more speed to sort or to search...)   


If you have a suggestion to include in a future releases of LR! please
@{"contact" LINK "Address"} us as soon as possible.
@ENDNODE

